
In PL/I constant 3.1415 = fixed decimal constant 

In PL/I a floating decimal constant MUST HAVE AN EXPONENT
  3.1415e0             //single
  3.141592e0           //double
  3.141592654589793e0  //quad 
****The number of digits p determines the size with the same rules
    as for the precision of variables 

You can explicity specify the size by using a different character
  before the exponenet value

  s = single precision     //3.1415s0
  d = double preceision    //3.1415d00
  q = quad precision       //3.1415q0

//FLOAT BINARY CONSTANTS
  Float binary constant is a sequence of bianry digits with a decimal
  point AND an exponent with a suffix of B(or b)
  Number of digits p determines the size
***USE SPARINGLY, HARD TO READ/FIGURE OUT
  11.0e0b    //float bin(3)
             // = decimal 3
  11.01e0b   //float bin(4)
             // = decimal 3.25 
